            You're a shoo-in.   

04:53.000 --> 04:55.400
I couldn't help but notice,     
for the last couple of days     

04:55.500 --> 04:57.500
you have just been sitting      
here doing nothing.             

04:59.800 --> 05:00.900
         Hi. I'm Norm Peterson. 

05:01.000 --> 05:02.200
      Obviously, we haven't met.

05:02.300 --> 05:03.500
This really bothers me.         

05:03.600 --> 05:04.600
                        Why?    

05:04.700 --> 05:06.200
 Because, because you           
have a job to do                

05:06.300 --> 05:07.700
     and instead, you           
  are just sitting here         

05:07.700 --> 05:09.000
talking to Cliff all day long.  

05:09.100 --> 05:10.800
I mean, you're                  
not even trying.                

05:10.900 --> 05:12.700
     Rebecca, do you <i>get</i> Cheers?

05:12.700 --> 05:14.700
              I mean, do you    
         understand the concept?

05:18.500 --> 05:20.700
    I want to see some work     
      by the end of today.      

05:20.800 --> 05:23.400
If you can't get the job done,  
I will hire a professional.     

05:23.400 --> 05:25.700
Oddly enough, that's what       
  Vera said on our honeymoon.   

05:30.200 --> 05:33.000
So, uh, how're you              
gonna get out of this one?      

05:33.100 --> 05:34.400
                  Relax, Cliffy,

05:34.400 --> 05:35.300
    I got it covered.           

05:35.400 --> 05:36.800
          I have a new          
industrial paint sprayer.       

05:36.800 --> 05:38.600
    Gets the job done           
     in a couple of hours.      

05:38.700 --> 05:39.700
Very clever.                    

05:39.800 --> 05:40.600
                      Mm-hmm.   

05:40.800 --> 05:42.200
                 It was invented
                 by the Japanese

05:42.200 --> 05:44.700
 so they could paint, you know, 
 more efficiently and quickly.  

05:44.700 --> 05:46.500
    Whereas you will use it     
      to drink more beers,      

05:46.600 --> 05:47.900
         watch more TV,         
     and put off everything     

05:48.000 --> 05:49.000
  until the very last minute.   

05:49.100 --> 05:50.800
        Right. You see,         
    they're way ahead of us     

05:50.900 --> 05:53.800
 in technology, but they don't  
      have our creativity.      

05:56.600 --> 05:59.100
Hey, Doc, how do you think      
