06:02.600 --> 06:04.600
                    Yeah.       

06:04.700 --> 06:06.100
        Where did you get it?   

06:06.100 --> 06:07.300
        Well...                 

06:07.400 --> 06:09.300
the first job                   
I ever had was, uh,             

06:09.400 --> 06:11.400
at this greasy spoon            
when I was 15.                  

06:11.500 --> 06:15.600
There was this old waitress     
     there, named Cora.         

06:15.700 --> 06:17.700
  She taught me everything      
I know about waiting tables.    

06:18.500 --> 06:20.800
Anyway, on, uh, her last day,   

06:20.900 --> 06:23.900
the day they were carting her   
off to the nursing home,        

06:23.900 --> 06:26.100
she gave me this bow.           

06:26.100 --> 06:27.700
      She told me               
 to wear it with pride          

06:27.700 --> 06:31.600
because being a waitress        
is a wonderful thing.           

06:31.600 --> 06:34.100
    Carla, that's quite a story.

06:34.100 --> 06:36.200
 Now, if the judges             
 are as sappy as you,           

06:36.200 --> 06:37.400
I get me a new car!             

06:37.500 --> 06:38.800
     (laughing)                 

06:40.700 --> 06:41.700
    Carla.                      

06:41.800 --> 06:42.700
     (clears throat)            

06:42.800 --> 06:44.200
 Honey, I just want you to know 

06:44.300 --> 06:48.000
that I've got some... moral     
problems with this contest.     

06:49.300 --> 06:51.600
 It's not gonna get in the way  
     of me hoping you win.      

06:51.700 --> 06:52.700
                    Yeah. Well, 
                    thanks, Sam.
          Yeah.                 

06:52.700 --> 06:54.300
          Now, would you give me
          my button over there? 

06:54.400 --> 06:56.300
            Oh.                 

06:56.400 --> 06:58.500
Here. "My name's Carla          
and I love your smile."         

06:58.600 --> 07:00.000
(chuckles):                     
      Here.                     

07:00.000 --> 07:02.200
Boy, you're really prepared     
to go all the way for this.     

07:02.300 --> 07:04.200
            Yeah. I got a button
            that says that, too.

07:04.300 --> 07:05.600
         Think I should wear it?

07:05.600 --> 07:07.600
    No, no. I'd stick           
  with the smile thing.         

07:07.700 --> 07:08.900
                    Right.      

07:09.000 --> 07:10.100
Could I have some service?      

07:10.100 --> 07:11.200
                         Coming!

07:13.700 --> 07:16.400
                Hi. I'll be     
            your waitress today.

07:16.500 --> 07:18.000
            How may I serve you?

07:18.100 --> 07:19.500
    I want a martini.           

07:19.500 --> 07:21.600
         Dry. D-R-Y.            

07:21.700 --> 07:23.400
And that means                  

07:23.400 --> 07:24.700
     light on the vermouth.     

07:24.700 --> 07:26.500
      And I want a twist,       
         not an olive.          

07:26.600 --> 07:27.700
                 Very well, sir.

07:27.700 --> 07:29.200
Uh, uh, read                    
that back to me.                

07:29.300 --> 07:31.700
I don't want any mistakes.      

07:31.800 --> 07:35.100
          One martini, very dry.

07:35.100 --> 07:36.500
     You forgot the twist.      

07:36.600 --> 07:38.400
          Twist it is.          

07:38.400 --> 07:40.400
  I'll twist his big ears off.  

07:40.400 --> 07:42.700
  Take it easy, take it easy.   

07:42.800 --> 07:44.800
      He wants a very dry       
     martini with a twist.      

07:54.600 --> 07:56.500
What'd you do that for?         

07:56.600 --> 07:58.200
          It's nothing personal.

07:58.200 --> 08:01.200
                  I was just    
